text: National Highway 312, commonly referred to as NH 312 is a national highway in India. It is a secondary route of National Highway 12. NH-312 runs in the state of West Bengal in India. == Route == NH312 connects Jangipur, Omarpur, Murshidabad, Chunakhali, Jalangi, Karimpur, Nazirpur, Tehatta, Krishnanagar, Hanshkhali, Duttapulia, Helencha, Bangaon, Berigopalpur Ghat, Ichamati, Tarnipur Ghat, Swarupnagar and Basirhat (Ghojadanga) in the state of West Bengal. == Junctions == : Terminal near Jangipur. : near Bangaon == See also == * List of National Highways in India * List of National Highways in India by state == References == == External links == * NH 312 on OpenStreetMap Category:National highways in India Category:National Highways in West Bengal
